article.headline: Maine 68, NJIT 58
article.story: NEWARK, N.J. (AP) -- Jon Sheets scored 19 points to lead Maine to a 68-58 win over the New Jersey Institute of Technology on Friday night. Junior Bernal and Mark Socoby both added 11 points for Maine (4-4), while Kevin Reed had nine points, eight rebounds, four assists and three steals for the Black Bears, who won for the fourth time in their last five games. Clayton Barker had a game-high 22 points for the Highlanders (2-5), who lost their fifth straight game. Mark Milbourne Swan added 10 points, while Dan Stonkus had 10 rebounds and three blocked shots. Maine was in command for most of the game and held several double-digit leads, but they had trouble putting away the feisty Highlanders, who shot just 34 percent from the floor but hit several key shots to keep within striking distance.
